<p>Hmm. I’m puzzled. Where did this come from? How did it know counter.v?</p>

<p>Mecrisp has an icestick version. Intriguing (Mecrisp is a forth implementation)</p>

<p>https://github.com/platformio/platform-lattice_ice40/tree/develop/examples/leds</p>

<p>had to sudo apt install libreadline6 and gtkwave to run simulation</p>

<p>I had to follow these instructions to get the FTDI device to work</p>

<p>https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36633819/iceprog-cant-find-ice-ftdi-usb-device-linux-permission-issue</p>

<p>and change the platformio.ini file to say icestick instead of icezum. Actually i don’t think that is necessary.</p>

